<h1>About Auto-Correct</h1>

<p>At Auto‑Correct Motors, we believe buying a car shouldn’t feel like filing taxes or assembling 
    IKEA furniture without the instructions. We’re a small but mighty dealership built on one 
    simple idea: car shopping should be honest, easy, and maybe even a little fun.
</p>

<p>We don’t do the whole “mysterious fees” thing.
We don’t do the “let me talk to my manager” dance.
We definitely don’t do the “this car was only driven by a little old lady on Sundays” routine.
</p>

<p>Instead, we do:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Transparent Pricing:</strong> What you see is what you get. No hidden fees, no last-minute surprises.</li>
    <li><strong>Quality Vehicles:</strong> Vehicles that actually run (wild concept, we know).</li>
    <li><strong>Service Requests:</strong> Our team is here to help you find the perfect car for your needs and budget, without any pressure.</li>
    <li><strong>Customer Reviews:</strong> That aren’t written by bots named “CarFan92”.</li>
    <li><strong>Employees:</strong> Who are helpful on purpose.</li>
    <li><strong>A little humor:</strong> Because car shopping should be fun, not stressful.</li>
</ul>

<div class="section-divider"></div>


<h2>Our Mission</h2>

<p>To help real people find real cars without the real headaches.
If we can make you laugh once along the way, that’s just good customer service.
</p>

<div class="section-divider"></div>


<h2>Our Team</h2>

<h3>Customers</h3>

<p>You’re the reason we exist. You browse, you review, you request oil changes at suspiciously 
    late hours — and we love you for it.
</p>

<h3>Employees</h3>

<p>The heroes who keep the wheels turning. They update vehicle details, manage service requests, 
    and bravely moderate reviews like “this car smells like my uncle’s basement.”
</p>

<h3>Admin/Owner</h3>

<p>The all‑seeing, all‑editing overlord who keeps the whole operation running smoothly. 
    If something breaks, they probably already fixed it.
</p>

<div class="section-divider"></div>


<h3>Why Choose Auto-Correct Motors?</h3>

<p>Because we’re the dealership that:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Treats you like a human</li>
    <li>Prices cars like we’ve touched a calculator before</li>
    <li>Lets you track your service requests like a pizza order</li>
    <li>Doesn’t hide the good stuff behind a login wall</li>
    <li>Actually reads your contact messages</li>
</ul>

<p>Also, our cars are pretty great.</p>

